flowRoot.flowPara: Begin with creatures on the square in front of their color. Each creature should initially have six symbols visible, indicating a strength of six. The monster player begins play.
The symbols visible on a given creature indicate which actions that creature is capable of. The number of symbols is that creature's strength.
The most common actions are moving and attacking.

Specific range actions are indicated with a circle, and can be activated by placing a range action die (showing circles) on the creature. All range actions take effect within a circle with radius two.
Special actions are indicted with a triangle. These consist of remaining aloft, casting a fireball spell, and paralyzing an opponent by turning them (reversibly) to stone with the basilisk's gaze.
